contents:
Pee Curiam:
The court below left the question of fact fairly to the jury, whether Catharine Dinan, wife of Michael Dinan, had a separate estate, and whether the property in controversy was acquired by means of, and upon the credit of that separate estate. The verdict of the jury settles the question of fact in her favor, and as no error of law appears the judgment must stand.
Judgment affirmed.
